  "summary": "1.Seawise Giant\nSeawise Giant was the longest self-propelled ship in history, built in 1974-1979. The heaviest self-propelled ship of any kind, and with a laden draft of 24.6 m (81 ft), she was incapable of navigating the English Channel,[5] the Suez Canal or the Panama Canal. She was sunk in 1988 during the Iran-Iraq War, but was later salvaged and restored to service.",
